name: Shane Herman
text:
First time visiting this Airport. Nice airfield.  Clean, well kept. Great scenery right after takeoff.
Not a pilot so I don't have that perspective to offer. We were here with a friend who is. I am an airfield electrician and work on runway and taxiway electrical systems so I know my way around an airfield. I have no idea about their systems on this field. I was just there as a visitor. Anyway it is a well kept airfield in a great location close enough to key areas.

name: LaTisha Byrd
text: This place will always hold some of my favorite memories. Growing up here fishing with my Dad will always be cherished times. Those early morning cool boat rides right before the sun breaches the horizon into a glorious display of God's creation won't be forgotten anytime soon. To carry that tradition on for our children is even more important. We love camping here. I miss the old pool house and getting snow cones after a hot summer swim. This place will forever hold a special place in my heart.

name: Steve Canerossi
text:
One of the best fish camps in the delta.  Parking can be a bit tight on popular weekends, so slip away during the week if you can.  If not, plan to arrive early or have a bit of a hike back to your boat.  The landing store sells a little bit of everything (except beer), and has a nice selection of lures and live bait.

They also offer cabins and a camp ground with full hook ups.  Make your reservations early as the folks who have been going there for years tend to book well in advance.

name: Graham Smith
text: This is the friendliest FBO I fly into.  We fly into Gulf Shores several times a year.  My needs are always met and they go out of their way to accommodate you. I am always happy to greet everyone at Platinum Aviation when we come to Gulf Shores.  They prove service and friendliness builds loyalty. The employees care and it shows.

name: Heath Lawrence
text: Extremely helpful and courteous staff here! Truly above and beyond. We had a tough time this past weekend, but the people at Platinum made it the best it could’ve been! First off, our Taxi no showed us, and there were no Lyft drivers available, so I desperately called the FBO for help finding a taxi. They didn’t send a taxi, they came and picked us up in their courtesy car! Then we burned up a starter in our Baron, so they let us borrow the courtesy car while we waited for rescue, and also gave the kids crayons and coloring books to keep them entertained while we waited! They even tried to find us a mechanic, but we didn’t get that lucky on a Sunday! So, on top of their great fuel prices and normal stuff they do a great job of, they went the extra mile, and then another mile, to make our crappy day a lot less crappy! This is definitely where I’ll go when I’m traveling to Gulf Shores again.

name: Patrick
text:
Top shelf FBO!  Flew in last night 8/24.  First time using platinum as my regular FBO wouldn’t answer the phone.  Platinum answered the call, let us use the crew car, topped off our tanks, and rolled out the carpet for our little Piper.  We were treated like we flew a GV.

Excellent facility and staff

Thank you for making our stop a delight.

name: Tyler Strate
text: Doug and Jeff at Albertville aviation are probably two of the friendliest, helpfull, take-the-shirt-off-their-back kind of guys I've ever had the pleasure of meeting and working  with at an FBO.  I flew into Albertville to take a CFI checkride. It was after hours when I flew in and tied down but Doug was there to help me out, got me a drink, set me up with his courtesy car for the night, and even got me a discount on my hotel room since he knew the owner! The next day durring my checkride he bought lunch for everyone, and even gave me a t-shirt after I passed my test! I will definitely stop in if I'm ever in the area and would recommend Albertville to anyone!

text:
Frontier is a decent airline with cheap fares. The airport is convenient but really small. It’s embarrassing for travelers to see a facility that doesn’t even have proper  tarmac, gangway, or an actual baggage carousel .  Literally people carry them off the plane onto a dolly and set them out in the main lobby/entrance area by staff members (untrained teenagers) and then just let all the people crowded around to cipher through all the bags to find your own luggage.
I can’t imagine this becoming the main airport for Mobile or it even being considered a international airport or hub. Very scary, but leave it to that $ pocketing mayor and old Mobilians..

Great people, excellent service.
